.TH VEK_INIT 3 "2024-01-01" "vek 0.8.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
vek_init \- initialize the vek library and detect CPU features
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <vek.h>
.sp
.BI "int vek_init(void);"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR vek_init ()
initializes the vek library and detects available CPU features (SSE2, AVX2,
AVX-512, NEON) to select the optimal SIMD backend.
.PP
This function is optional — it is called automatically on the first API call
via
.BR pthread_once (3).
Subsequent calls are no-ops.
.PP
The function is thread-safe. Multiple threads may call
.BR vek_init ()
concurrently without additional synchronization.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.BR vek_init ()
returns 0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH NOTES
After initialization,
.BR vek_backend_name (3)
returns the name of the selected backend.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vek_backend_name (3),
.BR vek_dot_f32 (3)
